HEADWORD: Dividuous
<hw>Di*vid"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dividuus</ets> divisible, divided, fr. <ets>dividere</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Divided; dividual.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He so often substantiates distinctions into <qex>dividuous</qex>,
selfsubsistent.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Divination</ent>⟦br⟧
